In order to observe the changes of a textfield input, you can observer the variable in a model. Removing the filtering logic from the view would be probably a good idea as well.
An example of this would be to start observing the `filterText` when the model inits. Also, remember to keep a reference to a cancellable returned from `sink`.
What we do here is every time the value from `filterText` changes (and it does because of textfield binding), we will filter the array and assign a value to the `activePeople` variable

```
 var filterCancellable: AnyCancellable?

    init() {
        filterCancellable = $filterText.sink {[weak self] currentText in
            guard let strongSelf = self else { return } 
            strongSelf.activePeople = strongSelf.filterList(with: currentText)
        }
    }

    func filterList(with text: String) -&gt; [Person] {
        if ( text == &quot;&quot; ) {
            return allPeople
        } else {
            return allPeople.filter( { $0.name.localizedStandardContains( text ) } )
        }
    }
```

This way you can later do just 
```
var body: some View {
        VStack {
            Form {
                Section {
                    TextField(&quot;Filter Text&quot;, text: $model.filterText)
                }
                Section {
                    Text( &quot;Filtered by: \(model.filterText)&quot; )
                    ForEach( model.activePeople ) { person in
                        Text( person.name )
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
```

